packets.parameters

Enum DataType

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<DataType>
      • packets.parameters.DataType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<DataType>

    public enum DataType
extends java.lang.Enum<DataType>
    FULLY DOCUMENTED. This is used to represent the various types of cmd and tlm parameters. This is used behind-the-scenes to read and write CCSDS packets.
    Author:
    Joe Benassi

    • Field Detail

      • dataTypes

        private static final DataType[] dataTypes
        All data types supported for a parameter. Each is either an integer, unsigned integer, or char. Each is either 8, 16, or 32 bit. Each is either a string or integer. This is used for byte packing or parsing.

      • type

        private final java.lang.String type

      • typeBytes

        private final int typeBytes

      • isString

        private final boolean isString

      • stringScalar

        private int stringScalar
        This is used when a parameter is a string of length 'stringScalar'. This stringScalar determines the amount of bytes allocated to a paramter, and is defined in an App Profile.

      • setStringScalar

        private final void setStringScalar(int stringScalar)
        Sets the string scalar. This is used to allocate extra bytes for a String that represents an array of this DataType. For example, the input value could be 20 (OS_MAX_PATH_LEN) if appropriate.
        Parameters:
        stringScalar - The string scalar.

      • getCmdParam

        public final CmdParam getCmdParam(java.lang.String name,
                   boolean isInputParam,
                   ChoiceOption[] choiceArray)
        Returns a CmdParam with the input properties of name, choice options, and if it is an inputparam.
        Parameters:
        name - The name of the parameter.
        isInputParam - If the desired CmdParam is an inputparameter.
        choiceArray - An array of ChoiceOptions. Can be size zero if this is an inputparam.
        Returns:
        A CmdParam with the input properties.

      • getDataType

        public static final DataType getDataType(java.lang.String type,
                   java.lang.String primitive,
                   java.lang.String bytes)
        Returns a DataType who has the desired type, primitive, and bytes.
        Parameters:
        type - The type of this DataType. For example, "uint8".
        primitive - The primitive of this DataType. If this starts with an "s", it is considered a string.
        bytes - The amount of bytes to allocate to this DataType if this is an integer (if this is DataType represents a String, this value will be multiplied by its StringScalar to determine its byte length).
        Returns:
        The DataType with the input properties.

      • getTlmStrArray

        public final java.lang.String getTlmStrArray(byte[] RawData,
                              int RawIndex)
        MAY NOT WORK WITH DATATYPES OF TYPE STRING. Used to parse telemetry CCSDS packets. Parses the data array between the indices (RawIndex) and (RawIndex + getBytes()) and converts it to a meaningful String to be displayed in the GUI.
        Parameters:
        RawData -
        RawIndex -
        Returns:
        A String representing the value of the telemetry.
